history.content:
Hi everyone! Girls Who Code at Berkeley is recruiting members and officers for Spring 2021! 
Girls Who Code is a national non-profit organization working to close the gender gap in technology. Our mission is to educate, equip, and inspire girls with the computing skills they'll need to pursue 21st-century opportunities. Along with reviewing @girlswhocode's custom curriculum, we will be creating our own college-level repository, hosting workshops and tech talks, and prepping for tech interviews.
APPLY HERE: https://linktr.ee/gwcberkeley
We currently have positions open for: 
  • Lead Developer
  • Director of Outreach and Engagement
  • Director of Finance
  • Education Curriculum Designer
  • Graphic Designer
The role descriptions will be linked in the application. We hope you join us! If you have any questions, please message us on Facebook or email us at gwcberkeley@gmail.com.
